<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-01T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/775: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-01T18:00:00+01:00">June
                                        1, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 1—1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>995. Marseilles and Lyons have just been bombarded by planes of
                                unidentified nationality. One ship in the harbor of Marseilles is on
                                fire. The <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi> positively must receive
                                orders at once not to enter the Mediterranean.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>